  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-06-24",
    "date": "2021-08-03T13:18:46Z",
    "text": "Zero-Emission Nuclear Power Production Credit Act of 2021\n\nThis bill allows a new business-related tax credit through 2031 for the production of electricity from zero-emission nuclear power. It also allows an election for direct payments of such credit and requires a recapture of the credit for contractors who pay their laborers or mechanics less than the prevailing wage rate.\n\nContractors must ensure that at least 15% of their work force is composed of qualified apprentices.\n\nThe bill requires the Government Accountability Office to report on the effectiveness the tax credit."
